[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run against the Apache Commons Compress tar-archiving code hit a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout. The fuzzer’s `fuzzerTestOneInput` entry point was executing [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TarFile`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`TarArchiveEntry` logic, and the JVM remained busy in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BigInteger.divideOneWord` for over [0m[1;36m27[0m[39m seconds without making progress. No explicit[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash or exception was reported—only a hang leading to a timeout.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer execution stalled [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtimed out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m inside Java’s big-integer arithmetic [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile processing PAX header timestamps in a TAR entry. The harness invoked `new [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mTarFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on fuzzed input, which triggered parsing of decimal-second timestamps[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia `TarArchiveEntry.parseInstantFromDecimalSeconds`.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Although no security exploit or crash is indicated, the behavior represents a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotential denial-of-service scenario [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzzer hang[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where specially crafted input [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcauses unbounded or extremely slow execution.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The main thread is in state RUNNABLE for [0m[1;36m27.9[0m[39m s, consuming CPU in [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MutableBigInteger.divideOneWord`.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The stack trace shows repeated calls through [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BigInteger.divideAndRemainderKnuth`, then into `BigDecimal.divideAndRound` and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39multimately `TarArchiveEntry.parseInstantFromDecimalSeconds`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • No other threads are blocked or contending on locks; the hang is purely [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputational.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`CompressTarFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simply constructs a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TarFile`, so the problematic code resides entirely in the tar-parsing library and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe JDK’s math routines.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **TarArchiveEntry.parseInstantFromDecimalSeconds** and related PAX header [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling in `TarArchiveEntry.processPaxHeader` and `updateEntryFromPaxHeaders`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The logic in `TarFile.paxHeaders` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `getNextTarEntry` that feeds those decimal[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstrings into `BigDecimal`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The use of `BigDecimal.divide` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `remainder` for arbitrary-precision [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing—particularly how extremely long or malformed decimal strings are handled.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Interactions between the fuzz harness and `TarFile` construction to understand[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhow input bytes map to the PAX header fields.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mglobalPaxHeaders, [0m[1;35mcurrEntry.getSize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m595[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m596[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m597[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m for [0m[1;36m0.1[0m[39m PAX Headers[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m598[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mheaders.containsKey[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTarGnuSparseKeys.MAP[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m599[0m[39m:            sparseHeaders = new [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mArrayList<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mTarUtils.parseFromPAX01SparseHeaders[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mheaders.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTarGnuSparseKeys.MAP[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m600[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m601[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mgetNextTarEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Get the actual file entry[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m602[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrEntry == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m603[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"premature end of tar archive. Didn't find [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32many entry after PAX header."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m604[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m605[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mapplyPaxHeadersToCurrentEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheaders, sparseHeaders[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m606[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m607[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m for [0m[1;36m1.0[0m[39m PAX Format, the sparse map is stored in the file data block[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m608[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcurrEntry.isPaxGNU1XSparse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m609[0m[39m:            try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream input = [0m[1;35mgetInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrEntry[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m610[0m[39m:                sparseHeaders = [0m[1;35mTarUtils.parsePAX1XSparseHeaders[0m[1;39m([0m[39minput, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecordSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m611[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m612[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mcurrEntry.setSparseHeaders[0m[1;39m([0m[39msparseHeaders[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m613[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m data of the entry is after the pax gnu entry. So we need to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdate the data position once again[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m614[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mcurrEntry.setDataOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcurrEntry.getDataOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + recordSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m615[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m616[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m617[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m sparse headers are all done reading, we need to build[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m618[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m sparse input streams using these sparse headers[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m619[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mbuildSparseInputStreams[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m620[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m621[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m622[0m[39m:    private void [0m[1;35mreadGlobalPaxHeaders[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m623[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream input = [0m[1;35mgetInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrEntry[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m625[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m626[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mgetNextTarEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Get the actual file entry[0m                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m: * An entry in a <a [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33mhref[0m[39m=[0m[32m"https[0m[32m://www.gnu.org/software/tar/manual/html_node/Standard.html"[0m[39m>Tar [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive<[0m[35m/[0m[95ma[0m[39m>.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m: * It consists of the entry's header, as well as the entry's File. Entries can [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe instantiated in one of three[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m: * ways, depending on how they are to be used.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m: * TarEntries that are created from the header bytes read from an archive are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstantiated with the [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link TarArchiveEntry#[0m[1;35mTarArchiveEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m constructor.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m: * These entries will be used when extracting from or listing the contents of an[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive. These entries have their header filled in using the header bytes. They[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m: * also set the File to null, since they reference an archive entry not a file.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m: * TarEntries that are created from Files that are to be written into an archive[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare instantiated with the [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link TarArchiveEntry#[0m[1;35mTarArchiveEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m or[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link TarArchiveEntry#[0m[1;35mTarArchiveEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m constructor. These entries have[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtheir header filled in using the File's information. They also keep a reference[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m: * to the File for convenience when writing entries.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m: * Finally, TarEntries can be constructed from nothing but a name. This allows [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe programmer to construct the entry by hand, for instance when only an[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m: * InputStream is available for writing to the archive, and the header [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minformation is constructed from other information. In this case the header fields [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare set[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m: * to defaults and the File is set to null.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m: * The C structure for a Tar Entry's header is:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m: * struct header [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m497[0m[39m:     * Computes the value contained in a byte buffer. If the most significant [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m541[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m542[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m543[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m544[0m[39m:     * For PAX Format [0m[1;36m1.[0m[39mX: The sparse map itself is stored in the file data [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock, preceding the actual file data. It consists of a series of decimal numbers[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m545[0m[39m:     * delimited by newlines. The map is padded with nulls to the nearest block[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundary. The first number gives the number of entries in the map. Following are[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m546[0m[39m:     * map entries, each one consisting of two numbers giving the offset and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize of the data block it describes.[0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/tar/TarUtils.jav[0m[1;92ma:663[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m672[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m663[0m[39m:                        read++;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m664[0m[39m:                        totalRead++;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m665[0m[39m:                        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtotalRead < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || headerSize >= [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && totalRead >= [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheaderSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m666[0m[39m:                            break;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m667[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m668[0m[39m:                        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mch == [0m[32m'='[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m end of keyword[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m669[0m[39m:                            final String keyword = [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcoll.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mStandardCharsets.UTF_8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m670[0m[39m:                            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Get rest of entry[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m671[0m[39m:                            final int restLen = len - read;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m672[0m[39m:                            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrestLen <= [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m only NL[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/tar/TarArchiveEntry.jav[0m[1;92ma:269[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m27[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m269[0m[39m:    private static Instant [0m[1;35mparseInstantFromDecimalSeconds[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String value[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrows IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m270[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate field values to prevent denial of service attacks with [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBigDecimal values [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee JDK-[0m[1;36m6560193[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m271[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mPAX_EXTENDED_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[1;35mER_FILE_TIMES_PATTERN.matcher[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvalue[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.matches[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m272[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Corrupted PAX header. Time field value is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32minvalid '"[0m[39m + value + [0m[32m"'"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m273[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m274[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m275[0m[39m:        final BigDecimal epochSeconds = new [0m[1;35mBigDecimal[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvalue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m276[0m[39m:        final long seconds = [0m[1;35mepochSeconds.longValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m277[0m[39m:        final long nanos = [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mepochSeconds.remainder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mBigDecimal.ONE[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.movePointRight[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m9[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.longValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Introduce an explicit maximum PAX record length to bound memory and CPU usage:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In TarUtils, define a new private constant:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Maximum allowed length of a single PAX header record [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength field[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final int MAX_PAX_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m KiB[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In both overloads of parsePaxHeaders [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe four-arg and deprecated three-arg [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mversions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, immediately after parsing the ASCII length string into `int len`, add:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlen < [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m || len > MAX_PAX_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"PAX header record length "[0m[39m + len +[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m" is invalid or exceeds maximum of "[0m[39m + MAX_PAX_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - A lower bound of [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m ensures at least “[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m a\n” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength + space + minimum [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontent + newline[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - The upper bound prevents huge allocations and unbounded downstream parsing.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Retain the existing `headerSize` logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhen headerSize ≥ [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but apply our [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX check when headerSize < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Harden timestamp‐parsing to prevent unbounded BigDecimal work:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Tighten the PAX timestamp regex in TarArchiveEntry to limit both integral and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfractional digits:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Limit integer part to [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m19[0m[39m digits, fraction to [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m digits:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final Pattern PAX_EXTENDED_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_FILE_TIMES_PATTERN =[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"-?\\d[0m[32m{[0m[32m1,19[0m[32m}[0m[32m([0m[32m?:\\.\\d[0m[32m{[0m[32m0,9[0m[32m}[0m[32m)[0m[32m?"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Enforce a maximum entire‐string length before constructing BigDecimal:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final int MAX_TIMESTAMP_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m e.g., sign + [0m[1;36m19[0m[39m digits[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ dot + [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m digits = [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static Instant [0m[1;35mparseInstantFromDecimalSeconds[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String value[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrows IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Ensure format and guard against DoS via overly long strings[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mvalue.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > MAX_TIMESTAMP_LENGTH[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              || ![0m[1;35mPAX_EXTENDED_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[1;35mER_FILE_TIMES_PATTERN.matcher[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvalue[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.matches[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Corrupted PAX header. Time field is invalid or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mtoo long: '"[0m[39m + value + [0m[32m"'"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Existing BigDecimal logic follows[0m[33m...[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve existing functionality:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All well‐formed PAX headers with reasonable numeric lengths [0m[1;39m([0m[39mup to [0m[1;36m19[0m[39m integral[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdigits and up to [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m fractional digits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m parse unchanged.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing behavior for non‐timestamp headers [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize, uid, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntouched.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness and fuzzing logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TarFile`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`TarArchiveEntry` public APIs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot modified; only internal parsing bounds are enforced.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification and side‐effect mitigation:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Bounded PAX record length prevents malicious inputs from triggering unbounded [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory allocation and forcing BigInteger.divideOneWord into prolonged computation.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tightening the timestamp regex aligns with ISO‐[0m[1;36m8601[0m[39m fractional‐second [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprecision [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnanosecond maximum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, avoiding needless rounding or divide‐and‐remainder [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwork on huge digit sequences.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The chosen limits [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m10[0m[39m KiB PAX record, [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m fractional digits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exceed any [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate TAR use case while decisively mitigating DoS via large headers.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If exceptionally large valid PAX records are in use [0m[1;39m([0m[39mindustrial TARs with huge[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, tests may need adjustments; however, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m KiB per PAX record is far above [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtypical usage.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No broad exception catching is added; invalid or oversized inputs are rejected[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mearly with `IOException`, surfacing corruption rather than hang.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Reference patterns in codebase:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar maximum‐length enforcement is idiomatic in other archive formats [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., ZIP extra‐field limits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Regex tightening mirrors patterns in TimeUtils or other libraries where [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfractional digits are capped for nanosecond precision.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. No external or harness code is modified. Existing tests for PAX handling and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimestamp parsing should continue to pass, as valid inputs remain within the new [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/24/25 15:19:02][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=253072;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=839591;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNI global refs: [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m, weak refs: [0m[1;36m0[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run against Commons Compress reported a libFuzzer timeout. The thread [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdump shows the main thread spinning in BigDecimal.divideOneWord invoked from [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTarArchiveEntry.parseInstantFromDecimalSeconds while processing a PAX header. To [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmitigate excessively large numeric fields, a patch was proposed that:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In TarUtils.java: introduces `MAX_PAX_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LENGTH` and rejects PAX record [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlengths outside a valid range.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In TarArchiveEntry.java: tightens the timestamp regex, adds [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_TIMESTAMP_LENGTH`, and rejects overly long timestamp strings before converting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto BigDecimal.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the Maven build failed with syntax errors in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTarArchiveEntry.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`illegal start of type` and missing semicolons[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so the patch[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcannot be compiled as-is.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer encountered an ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout after ~[0m[1;36m28[0m[39m s.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The full thread dump reveals the “main” thread stuck in  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `java.math.MutableBigInteger.divideOneWord` → `BigDecimal.divide` →  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `TarArchiveEntry.parseInstantFromDecimalSeconds` → PAX header processing.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates pathological input [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvery large decimal strings[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m causing [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBigDecimal division to spin, triggering a timeout in the fuzz harness.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The hang occurs inside `TarArchiveEntry.processPaxHeader` when parsing a PAX [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield named something like “mtime” stored as a decimal seconds string.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other exceptions are thrown; the code never bounds the length of the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumeric field or length prefixes when reading PAX headers.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer entry point is `CompressTarFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput` which opens [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe archive via `new [0m[1;35mTarFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. The root cause is in core PAX header parsing.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `TarUtils.java` at the PAX record‐length parsing loop:  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Added `MAX_PAX_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • After reading the numeric length field [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, reject if `< [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m` or `> [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_PAX_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LENGTH`, throwing an `IOException`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `TarArchiveEntry.java`:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Modified the `PAX_EXTENDED_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_FILE_TIMES_PATTERN` regex from [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`-?\d[0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m19[0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m([0m[39m?:\.\d*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m?` to `-?\d[0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m19[0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m([0m[39m?:\.\d[0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m9[0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m?`.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Introduced `MAX_TIMESTAMP_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msign + [0m[1;36m19[0m[39m digits + dot + [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m digits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • In `parseInstantFromDecimalSeconds`, added a length check `[0m[1;35mvalue.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_TIMESTAMP_LENGTH` before regex matching; throw `IOException` if invalid.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Application and Build Log  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch was applied to the checked-out Commons Compress snapshot.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `mvn package` recompiled [0m[1;36m406[0m[39m sources.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation errors in `TarArchiveEntry.java`:  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Lines [0m[1;36m221[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m report “illegal start of type”, “[0m[32m';'[0m[39m expected”, and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“<identifier> expected”.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The errors point to malformed Java syntax, likely due to incorrect indentation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor stray line markers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m221[0m[39m:`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the patch.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review PAX header reading in `TarUtils` to ensure length parsing and record [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskipping logic is robust.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inspect `TarArchiveEntry.parseInstantFromDecimalSeconds` for correct placement[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof new constants, regex, and exception logic.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify code formatting and ensure constants and regex definitions are within [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass scope without line‐number prefixes.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Audit other numeric‐parsing routines in the TAR archiver for similar [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munbounded-memory or CPU risks.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
